      "body" : "Concept NACK. Although it's useful for your specific, narrow use-case. Which is good for you, but I don't think it warrants merging and maintaining this code.\r\n\r\nFWIW what I always do to create a pre-synced node (for testing, or fast deployment) is to use [fastcopy-chaindata](https://github.com/bitcoin-core/bitcoin-maintainer-tools#fastcopy-chaindata) to quickly create a clone of an existing blockchain state, then run bitcoind with prune option on the cloned state once.\r\n",
